{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/hiv-infection-aids/goals-outcome-measures/goals/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"da045857-e127-5b13-806b-efd61a584eed","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field cc60bac1-d413-4bd7-9b22-0ac3b1ec263f --><h2>Goals</h2><!-- end field cc60bac1-d413-4bd7-9b22-0ac3b1ec263f -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item c94477e1-c44f-43a5-9527-c045540a8dc0 --><!-- begin field 87438745-712e-455c-820c-61e81c164923 --><p>To support primary healthcare professionals to:</p><ul><li>Recognize problems that may be HIV-related and risk factors for HIV to help diagnose HIV infection as early as possible.</li><li>Give advice on health promotion, sexual and reproductive health, and mental health issues to people living with HIV.</li><li>Recognize HIV-related conditions that require urgent referral or admission.</li><li>Be aware of the potential for serious adverse effects and drug interactions associated with antiretroviral therapy (ART).</li><li>Identify and encourage people who will not attend specialist care for HIV management.</li><li>Care for people with end-stage disease.</li><li>Refer appropriately for post-exposure prophylaxis (PEP).</li><li>Be aware of the role of pre-exposure prophylaxis (PrEP) in prevention of HIV and signpost to appropriate services.</li></ul><!-- end field 87438745-712e-455c-820c-61e81c164923 --><!-- end item c94477e1-c44f-43a5-9527-c045540a8dc0 -->","topic":{"id":"6c2470d2-9bde-5a16-91a3-b5ed74ce2d2b","topicId":"23723770-8df0-4d05-aa4f-806db67f71df","topicName":"HIV infection and AIDS","slug":"hiv-infection-aids","lastRevised":"Last revised in July 2020","chapters":[{"id":"a83635cf-fad1-569e-8fec-1e53dd8ae096","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"21903de2-55a7-5de1-8f40-7d516cf2a7ba","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subC